cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a neuromorphic in-vehicle visual odometry system using feature tracking algorithm, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of bio-inspired vision sensors, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The system also involves machine learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
